"flightless-dung-beetle":{n:"Flightless Dung Beetle",c:"Insect",s:"Beetle",sz:"Small",cl:"Black",i:"ğŸª²",wp:"Circellium_bacchus",d:"Addo's most famous tiny resident. This large flightless dung beetle is endemic to the Eastern Cape. They roll elephant dung into balls for food and nesting. Have official right-of-way on all roads â€” running over one carries a fine. Critical for nutrient recycling.",w:"10-15 g",l:"3-4 cm",life:"2-3 years",act:"Diurnal",diet:"Coprophage â€” elephant dung",cs:"Vulnerable"},
